<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6189] If the node hosting a replica is not &quot;live&quot;, then leader-initiated recovery may publish the &quot;down&quot; state more than once.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6189</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In ZkController#ensureReplicaInLeaderInitiatedRecovery, the leader will publish the &quot;down&quot; state for a replica more than once if the node is not live. This is inefficient and can cause too many state change events to occur, one is sufficient.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
